context.arch.intelligibility.expression
Class ComparableRange<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

java.lang.Object
  context.arch.intelligibility.expression.ComparableRange<T>

public class ComparableRange<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Object

Continuous range that can specify whether the bounds are inclusive or exclusive. This is similar to org.apache.commons.lang.math.NumberRange. Easiest to think of this as a Number range, but it also applies to any Comparable object
